WLC_POINTER_GET_ORIGIN(3)                                WLC CORE API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_pointer_get_origin - aquire mouse pointer position

SYNOPSIS

    void wlc_pointer_get_origin(struct wlc_origin *out_origin);

DESCRIPTION

    Aquire the position of the mouse pointer relative to the currently focused
    output.  The position returned is relative to the time it was called.
    
EXAMPLE

    #include <wlc/wlc.h>

    struct wlc_origin origin;

    wlc_pointer_get_origin(&origin);
    move_pointer_to_view(view, &origin);
